HEADWORD: Unsex
<hw>Un*sex"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p.
p.</pos> <conjf>Unsexed</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb. n.</pos>
<conjf>Unsexing</conjf>.]</vmorph> <ety>[1st pref. <ets>un-</ets> +
<ets>sex</ets>.]</ety> <def>To deprive of sex, or of qualities becoming
to one's sex; esp., to make unfeminine in character, manners, duties, or
the like; <as>as, to <ex>unsex</ex> a woman</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Unsexual</ent>⟦br⟧
